# Design Review

Automated frontend design review using Playwright MCP for live browser testing. Evaluates UI changes against world-class standards (Stripe, Airbnb, Linear) across 8 phases: preparation, interaction flows, responsiveness, visual polish, accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA), robustness, code health, and content/console checks.

## When to Use

- Reviewing PRs with UI/UX changes
- Verifying visual consistency and accessibility compliance
- Testing responsive design across viewports (desktop 1440px, tablet 768px, mobile 375px)
- Ensuring new UI meets design system standards

## Requirements

- **Playwright MCP server** must be configured and running
- A live preview environment (dev server) accessible via browser
- Project design principles doc (use `design-principles-example.md` as starting template)

## Components

| File | Type | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| `design-review-agent.md` | Agent | Subagent definition for `@agent-design-review` |
| `design-review-slash-command.md` | Slash command | `/design-review` command that auto-diffs and reviews |
| `design-review-claude-md-snippet.md` | CLAUDE.md snippet | Add to project CLAUDE.md for quick visual checks |
| `design-principles-example.md` | Reference | S-tier SaaS design checklist template |

## Setup

1. Copy `design-review-agent.md` to `<project>/.claude/agents/design-review.md`
2. Copy `design-review-slash-command.md` to `<project>/.claude/commands/design-review.md`
3. Add contents of `design-review-claude-md-snippet.md` to your project's CLAUDE.md
4. Customize `design-principles-example.md` for your project and place in `<project>/context/design-principles.md`

## Review Output

Issues are triaged as:
- **[Blocker]** -- critical failures requiring immediate fix
- **[High-Priority]** -- significant issues to fix before merge
- **[Medium-Priority]** -- improvements for follow-up
- **[Nitpick]** -- minor aesthetic details

